cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.HC. 

The paper presents a natural language interface for describing high-level task specifications for robots, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and task planning. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a semantic parser, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses user studies and the gradual growth of a more natural task specification language, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
